Subject:Re: [anti-abuse-wg] RIPE NCC's proposed implementation of Abuse
	Contact Management in the RIPE Database
* Kaveh Ranjbar:

> Abuse handling is generally a role within an organisation and the
> RIPE NCC is planning to model this relation in the RIPE Database. So
> the "abuse-c:" attribute will be available in the ORGANISATION
> object and should reference a ROLE object. When a ROLE object is
> referenced from an ORGANISATION object by the "abuse-c:" attribute,
> it must have an "abuse-mailbox:" attribute.

Doesn't this invite mingling of allegedly privacy-relevant data and
abuse contact information?

